hints.content:
We can represent our work with division, too. We make groups of $\purpleD{2}$ equal parts.

$\begin{align}
\dfrac{\maroonD{2}}{\blueE{4}} &=\dfrac{\maroonD{2} \div\purpleD{2}}{\blueE{4}\div \purpleD{2}}\\\\
&= \dfrac{\maroonD{1}}{\boxed{\blueE{2}}}
\end{align}$

The area does not change.
